cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.DM

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the spread of behavior in social networks. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it uses computational methods to study social phenomena. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as it involves modeling the behavior of individual agents in a network. The paper also uses algorithms and data structures, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
